## Step 14 - location-priority-over-transport-cache
Done
Restructured `_beginConnect` in `camera-panel.js` to check the camera `location` (`local` / `external`) before consulting the cached `preferredTransport`, so any camera that the user explicitly placed in a Tailscale-reachable subnet always tries the direct MJPEG stream first regardless of stale session-cached fallback decisions; raised `connectTimeoutMs` to 12 s and `probeTimeoutMs` to 3 s to tolerate Tailscale relay latency.
Re-synced the updated panel into the embedded `cameraPanelJs` function in `flow.json` and validated the whole flow parses cleanly so the Node-RED runtime now serves the new connect-priority behavior.

## Step 15 - tailscale-route-diagnostic-and-proxy-stability
