## Step 36 - empty-device-list-on-flow-start
Done
Documented data path: the UI loads devices via `GET /api/devices` (`apiForNewDevice` in `flow.json`), which builds `merged` from `global.get(\"devices\")` plus `global.get(\"lastGoodPositionByDevice\")` for stale-GPS fallback; each OwnTracks/MQTT message through function node `09ecbcb7cc6bb1f7` (`Tracking-Logik`) does `global.set(\"devices\", devices)` with keyed entries `user/device`.
Set the `initialize` hook on that same `Tracking-Logik` node to `global.set(\"devices\", {})`, `global.set(\"lastGoodPositionByDevice\", {})`, and `global.set(\"lastPosition\", null)` so every deploy/restart shows an empty list until new positions arrive (saved places/routes globals are untouched).

## Step 37 - deploy-empty-device-list-vs-mqtt-retain
Done
Retained OwnTracks MQTT payloads were refilling `global.devices` immediately after deploy, so `initialize` alone looked ineffective; added `global.set(\"__deviceIngestSilenceUntil\", Date.now() + 4000)` in the same `initialize` and an early return in `Tracking-Logik` when `Date.now() < __deviceIngestSilenceUntil` so ingest is skipped during that window (no RAM ŌĆ£device registryŌĆØ from retained replay).
Added tab `Tracking` inject `e7d3a1c004f14298` (`once` + `onceDelay` 4.5s) ŌåÆ function `clearDeviceGlobalsDelayed` (`e7d3a1c004f14299`) that clears the same globals again and sets `__deviceIngestSilenceUntil` to `0` so live points work after deploy; mirrored the silence guard in the standalone `Tracking-logik` file for parity. Long-term persistence is still Node-RED `contextStorage` (file) if enabledŌĆöexclude `devices` there or move to a DB when ready.

## Step 38 - devices-api-live-session-only
Done
Rewrote `apiForNewDevice` (`flow.json` `1ecd66ddf2a0a1cc`) so `GET /api/devices` returns only `global.devices` entries with valid coordinates whose `receivedAt` is on or after `global.__trackingSessionEpoch`; dropped merging `lastGoodPositionByDevice` into that list so stale or file-restored ŌĆ£ghostŌĆØ devices no longer appear as selectable rows after deploy.
`Tracking-Logik` `initialize` now sets `__trackingSessionEpoch` to the same `Date.now()` tick as the silence window and clears `devices` / `lastGoodPositionByDevice` / `lastPosition` first, so the mapŌĆÖs device list stays empty until a post-deploy MQTT point is accepted (UI ŌĆ£VerbundenŌĆØ still follows `receivedAt` freshness in `Maplogik`).

